+# 🔗 onUpdate_Connection.md
+
+File: `Robotic_Systems/6_Connection/`
+Phase 6 of 9. The system stops working in isolation and checks in — client, collaborator, or just the next version of yourself.
+
+---
+
+## 🎯 Purpose
+
+Documents the intention behind the Connection phase: surfacing status to whoever needs it, in whatever form they need it in.
+
+---
+
+## ✍️ Authored by
+
+**<brforeal.dev@gmail.com>**
+
+🕯️ Seed Date: **April 13, 2025**
+
+---
+
+## 💡 Description
+
+Connection is the phase where the Upwork tracker and the journal actually leave the repo — a status update, a PR description, a README note for whoever picks this up next. Nothing gets built here. Something gets communicated. That distinction matters: Connection fails if it turns into another Action phase.
+
+---
+
+## 🧬 Philosophy
+
+> "Work nobody hears about isn't done yet — it's just private."
+> — Numerology-Cycle-9
+
+---
+
+## 🧠 Connected Modules
+
+- `/upworkTracker.js` — Deliverable summary source
+- `/journalStore.js` — Snapshot data for status updates
+- `README.md` — Where Connection output usually lands
